# Cross-doc consistency

When changing any of:
- `docs/state-snapshotter-rework/spec/system-spec.md`
- `docs/state-snapshotter-rework/architecture/overview.md` (or added `system-overview.puml`)
- `docs/state-snapshotter-rework/design/implementation-plan.md`
- `docs/state-snapshotter-rework/testing/e2e-testing-strategy.md`
- `docs/state-snapshotter-rework/operations/project-status.md`

check consistency (no contradiction) at least on:
- registry state vs runtime watch activation
- DSC conditions (`Accepted`, `RBACReady`, derived `Ready`) and watch activation formula
- optional unified CRD / bootstrap (S1–S2) vs future DSC-driven registry
- manifest / MCR track vs unified snapshot registry (separate concerns)
- stage / progress in `project-status.md` vs tables in `implementation-plan.md` and test IDs in `e2e-testing-strategy.md`

Related long-form ADR under `snapshot-rework/` must not disagree with `spec/system-spec.md` without an explicit documented transition.

Fix inconsistencies in the same change or document a temporary divergence and follow-up.
